HEADWORD: Photomicrograph
<hw>Pho`to*mi"cro*graph</hw>
<pr>(f⟦omac⟧`t⟦osl⟧*m⟦imac⟧"kr⟦osl⟧*gr⟦adot⟧f)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Photo-</ets> + <ets>micro</ets> + <ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>An enlarged or macroscopic photograph of a microscopic
object. See <er>Microphotograph</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A microscopically small photograph of an
object.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Photomicrography</ent>⟦br⟧
